<sect1 id='Converting'>
    <title>Converting DocBook files</title>
    	   <para>To convert an XML DocBook file on IndicoDev, for this example we shall use mydb.xml:</para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
	    <para>HTML, with each chapter/section on a seperate page (first page will be called index.html when produced)<screen>docbook2html mydb.xml</screen><emphasis>Note: Any images used need to be copied to correct directory for use with HTML applies to all HTML conversions</emphasis></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	 <para>HTML, all one document <screen>docbook2html --nochunks  mydb.xml > mydb.html</screen></para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	<para>PDF <screen>docbook2pdf  mydb.xml</screen> This seems to produce a section of unwanted text at the beginning when using a book form of DocBook (Tibor has been looking into why) Article format works fine</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
	    <para>PLAIN TEXT, need to have converted to html first <screen>w3m mydb.html > mydb</screen></para>
      </listitem>
     </itemizedlist>
 </sect1>

